      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so im having a really hard time sleeping lately. like i can barely stay asleep for more than a couple hours. i already take melatonin every night but it doesnt really seem to be doing much anymore. my doctor prescribed me some Ambien (zolpidem) to help me out, but i was wondering if it's okay if i take both at the same time? i figure if i take the melatonin with the Ambien it might help them work better together so i can actually get a full night of sleep.",
